\PYG{g+gu}{\PYGZsh{}\PYGZsh{} D — Architecture compliance (15 pts)}

Verifies the generated code follows the project structure from the guidelines.

| \PYGZsh{} | Check | Points | How to evaluate |
|\PYGZhy{}\PYGZhy{}\PYGZhy{}|\PYGZhy{}\PYGZhy{}\PYGZhy{}|\PYGZhy{}\PYGZhy{}\PYGZhy{}|\PYGZhy{}\PYGZhy{}\PYGZhy{}|
| D1 | Spec file location | 2 | File exists at \PYG{l+s+sb}{`e2e/\PYGZob{}plan\PYGZhy{}name\PYGZcb{}.spec.ts`}. Award 2 if correct, 0 if missing or wrong path. |
| D2 | POM file exists | 3 | A Page Object class exists in \PYG{l+s+sb}{`support/pages/`} for this feature. Award 3 if present with at least navigation and assertion methods. Award 1 if the file exists but is minimal/empty. Award 0 if missing. |
| D3 | Fixture file exists | 3 | A fixture file exists in \PYG{l+s+sb}{`fixtures/`} using \PYG{l+s+sb}{`test.extend\PYGZlt{}T\PYGZgt{}()`}. Award 3 if present and exports \PYG{l+s+sb}{`test`}. Award 1 if the file exists but doesn\PYGZsq{}t follow the \PYG{l+s+sb}{`test.extend`} pattern. Award 0 if missing. |
| D4 | Routes from routes.ts | 4 | Route paths in POM and spec are imported from \PYG{l+s+sb}{`support/data/routes.ts`} — no hardcoded path strings like \PYG{l+s+sb}{`\PYGZsq{}/hr/people\PYGZsq{}`} or \PYG{l+s+sb}{`\PYGZsq{}/employee/\PYGZsq{}`}. Award 4 if fully compliant. Deduct 1 per hardcoded route, minimum 0. |
| D5 | Auth via storageState | 3 | Feature tests do not call login functions or import \PYG{l+s+sb}{`loginHelpers`}. Auth is inherited from the Playwright config\PYGZsq{}s \PYG{l+s+sb}{`storageState`} setup. Award 3 if compliant. Award 0 if manual login logic is present. |

