\PYG{g+gu}{\PYGZsh{}\PYGZsh{} E — Data \PYGZam{} mock integrity (10 pts)}

Verifies real API usage, no mocks, and proper test data conventions.

| \PYGZsh{} | Check | Points | How to evaluate |
|\PYGZhy{}\PYGZhy{}\PYGZhy{}|\PYGZhy{}\PYGZhy{}\PYGZhy{}|\PYGZhy{}\PYGZhy{}\PYGZhy{}|\PYGZhy{}\PYGZhy{}\PYGZhy{}|
| E1 | No mock/intercept calls | 4 | Spec and POM must not use \PYG{l+s+sb}{`page.route(`}, \PYG{l+s+sb}{`page.unroute(`}, or any request interception. Award 4 if absent. Award 0 if any found. |
| E2 | No hardcoded credentials | 3 | No password strings, email literals, or credential values in spec or fixture. Credentials must come from \PYG{l+s+sb}{`constants.ts`} or environment variables. Award 3 if clean. Deduct 1 per violation, minimum 0. |
| E3 | E2E\PYGZus{} data prefix | 3 | Persistent test data (created entities, titles, names) uses the \PYG{l+s+sb}{`E2E\PYGZus{}`} prefix. Award 3 if all test data follows the convention. Award 1 if partially followed. Award 0 if no \PYG{l+s+sb}{`E2E\PYGZus{}`} prefix is used despite creating data. \PYG{g+gs}{**If the test is read\PYGZhy{}only and creates no data, award full points.**} |
